name: politico
text:
Listen to POLITICO Dispatch daily for quick, digestible analysis of the latest news on the pandemic, the election, and more. Subscribe today.
https://t.co/DPUpEFlsul https://t.co/hZMfBDDNeQ

name: politico
text: A senior adviser to Trump’s reelection campaign doubled down on baseless allegations leveled by the president that U.S. doctors are inflating coronavirus deaths for profit as the country sees record levels of new infections https://t.co/HC4nCLqTZi

name: politico
text: Florida Republican Sen. Rick Scott says he hopes the state is able to declare a winner of the presidential race on election night https://t.co/TvBEn1nmUa

name: politico
text: This year is the big test: Is Arizona flippable? And what role will Latinos, who are predominantly of Mexican origin, play in making it happen? https://t.co/o93ug9eIEI

name: politico
text: Democrats remain fretful that Black voter participation in Florida will lag as it did four years ago when Donald Trump beat Hillary Clinton in the state https://t.co/ibpOh102Te

name: politico
text: A federal court in Houston is holding an emergency hearing Monday morning over a last-ditch effort by Republicans in Texas to toss out nearly 127,000 ballots in a Democratic-leaning county https://t.co/0NZoTOyEv2

name: politico
text:
Election Day is upon us, and the battle for control of the Senate remains a coin flip. How are the pivotal races playing out? Can the Senate GOP hold the line? Subscribe to Huddle, our play-by-play guide to Congress, for the latest.
https://t.co/dfpSNWPYfR https://t.co/RnHra08YLY

name: politico
text:
Election administrators have been scrambling to prepare for Tuesday ever since the coronavirus turned a series of primaries into disasters this spring. 

Now, all they can do is wait and see if their efforts pay off. https://t.co/PZhaqc3fPd

name: politico
text: Joe Biden’s campaign fundraising efforts have quietly turned toward raising additional money for a possible post-Election Day legal fight with President Donald Trump that could stretch through November https://t.co/KbtQlTRhXV

name: politico
text: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden holds a single-digit lead over President Donald Trump in Pennsylvania, according to a new survey of the swing state that could determine control of the White House https://t.co/8lrFaHfpxx

name: politico
text:
When Republicans seized control of Congress and the White House in 2016, lobbyists with ties to President Donald Trump and powerful GOP lawmakers saw their stock skyrocket. 

Tuesday’s election could sweep all of that away. https://t.co/cZ0Ho5a0Gg

name: politico
text:
Media reports indicate President Trump may try to message false insinuations about which ballots can be counted ahead of what will likely be a lengthy process.

But it's important to remember that states run elections, not candidates or television networks
https://t.co/CAEICj4P00

name: politico
text: Wall Street can handle pretty much any election outcome other than total uncertainty and perhaps protests and violence in the streets. That is the biggest risk.  https://t.co/39gYkgE2GY
